New Homes in Myrtle Beach, South Carolina are Waiting for You
Myrtle Beach is a beautiful city with a lot to offer, and you can find a brand new home in a great location with D.R. Horton. We will work closely with you to determine your needs, wants and budget, and help you find the right home as quickly and easily as possible.
We have been building homes across the country for more than 35 years, and we’ve brought all our experience and dedication to these new homes in Myrtle Beach. Check out these communities of homes for sale in Brunswick County, new homes in Conway, SC, and many other incredible locations to find out why we’ve been named America’s #1 homebuilder since 2002. 


Discover Your New Home Options
These new homes are built with our trademark open design philosophy, and our unique floorplans offer a lot of great options for you and your family. Whether you’re looking for something simple and cozy or a home that has plenty of room to grow into, we make it easy to find quality, beautiful homes at a great price.
These homes have a wide range of options, including:

      - 1,400 to more than 3,700 square feet
      - 2 to 5 bedrooms
      - 1- or 2-story designs
      - 2.5, 3, 3.5 or 4 bathrooms
      - 1-, 2- or 3-car garage

Prices in many of these communities start in the low $170s, and they all still have beautiful exteriors, energy efficient features, and one of the most robust home warranties in the industry. 
Take a look at our current availabilities and find the one that meets your needs.
Living the Life in Myrtle Beach
With the beautiful, sandy beaches and the big hotels, one might mistake Myrtle Beach for a resort city in Florida. While Myrtle Beach certainly has its share of tourism, it also holds onto a sense of community which means the residents get to experience a range of great recreational activities, unique events and hidden gems that are available throughout the year.
This city is bordered by North Myrtle Beach and Surfside Beach, so no matter where you go, you’ll be surrounded by great scenery and opportunities for some fun in the sun.
If you’d like to know more about the area, be sure to check out:


The wide range of recreational activities 


The various events happening now


The official city page for help on moving to the area


